-- Vietnam Equity Mover Column: PetroVietnam Fertilizer, Dry Cell
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-05-08T07:53:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/vietnam-equity-mover-column-petrovietnam-fertilizer-dry-cell.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Vietnam trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Ho Chi Minh City.
The  VN Index (VNINDEX) , the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange, added 0.4 percent to 488.07, the highest close
since March 11, 2011.  PetroVietnam Fertilizer & Chemical Joint-Stock Co. (DPM)  , the country’s biggest listed fertilizer producer, rose 3.8
percent to 40,800 dong, the highest close since Feb. 17, 2011.
The company will pay its shareholders a dividend of 2,500 dong a
share on June 11, it said in a statement on the bourse’s
website.  Dry Cell & Storage Battery Joint-Stock Co. (PAC VN), a
battery maker and garment exporter, increased 4.7 percent to
24,500 dong, the highest close since April 25. The company will
pay a 2011 dividend of 1,400 dong a share in June, it said in a
statement on the exchange’s website.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
